<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1935-03-02T14:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1935-03-02T14:00:00-05:00" n="33" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d33">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">500.A15A4 General Committee
                                (Arms)/115b: Telegram</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of
                                        State</gloss> to the Ambassador in the United Kingdom</hi>
                                    (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Bingham</hi></persName>)</head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1935-03-02T14:00:00-05:00">March
                                        2, 1935—2 p.m.</date>
                                </dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>40. We are at a loss to understand the attitude of the British
                                Delegation at Geneva toward important elements of our Draft
                                Convention on Arms Manufacture and Trade and would appreciate
                                receiving your analysis as to the motives for this stand and as to
                                the likelihood of its modification in the course of further
                                discussion.</p>
                            <p>Please repeat this telegram and your reply to Amdelgat Geneva.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Phillips</hi>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>